or MX missile components.                                                                                                          A joint venture of Textron Inc. and Boeing Co. received a$31.5 million Navy contract for development of the V-22aircraft.   Boeing also received a $21.3 million Air Force contractfor engineering services. And the company's Boeing ComputerServices received a $15.8 million Army contract forautomation systems.                                                                                                          Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of General Motors Corp., wasawarded a $23.3 million Navy contract for a targeting system.General Motors also got a $17.5 million Navy contract foraircraft engines.                                                                                                          Zantop International Airlines received a $23.2 million AirForce contract for air transportation services.                                                                                                          Martin-Baker Aircraft Co. was given a $19 million Navycontract for aircraft ejection seats.                                                                                                          ITT Corp. received an $18 million Army contract for aradar jammer.                                                                                                          Computer Sciences Corp. won a $15.3 million Army contractfor automation systems.                                                                                                          Republic Corp. was issued a $14.7 million Air Forcecontract for C-130 aircraft overhaul.                                                                                                          GTE Government Systems Corp., a unit of GTE Corp., won a$12 million Army contract for communications equipment.</TEXT></DOC>